headline: Minimum Wage Increases Could Lower Suicide Rates, Study Says
abstract: It was the latest study to suggest that effects of wage increases reach beyond economic welfare, but some experts pushed back on the findings.
lead_paragraph: Raising the minimum wage could lower the suicide rate, according to a study published last week, delivering labor advocates a tantalizing new finding about the broader impacts of wage changes even as some experts said other factors could explain the decrease.
